"$:/plugins/yaisog/taggingtree-filter/readme": {
    "created": "20230202121752836",
    "text": "|!purpose |select all descendants of the input tiddlers recursively |
|!input |a selection of titles |
|!parameter |ignored |
|!output |all descendants of the input tiddlers, recursively |


The `taggingtree` filter operator is used to select all descendants of the input tiddlers. Descendants are all tiddlers that have the input tiddlers as a tag (i.e. their //children//), all tiddlers that have the //children// as a tag (i.e. their //grandchildren//), and so forth.

It would be equivalent to using an infinite subfilter like

```
[tagging[]] [tagging[]tagging[]] [tagging[]tagging[]tagging[]] ...
```
The first run will return all children, the second run all grandchildren, the third run all great-grandchildren, ...<br>
Infinite (or recursive) filters cannot be defined in ~TiddlyWiki, however.

The `taggingtree` operator contains a filter to avoid infinite loops.

Its companion filter, `tagstree`, selects all //ancestors// of the input titles.

!! Examples
!!! Filtering search results
Together with the [[tagstree|$:/plugins/yaisog/tagstree-filter]] operator, `taggingtree` can be used to filter search results by tag, where only the tags that are actual ancestors of the search result tiddlers are presented for selection, instead of //all// tags in the wiki. The search result is then intersected with the list of descendants of the selected filter tag in order to only show results that are also descendants of that tag.

```
<$set name="searchResults" filter=<some filtering operation> >
	<$select tiddler="$:/temp/search-select" default="all tags">
		<option value="all tags">all tags</option>
		<$list filter="[enlist<searchResults>tagstree[]]">
			<option value=<<currentTiddler>>><<currentTiddler>></option>
		</$list>
	</$select>

	<$set name="tagFilter" filter="[{$:/temp/search-select}match[all tags]]" value="[all[]]" emptyValue="[all[]] :intersection[{$:/temp/search-select}taggingtree[]]">
		<$list filter="[enlist<searchResults>subfilter<tagFilter>]" template="$:/core/ui/ListItemTemplate" />
	</$set> <!-- tagFilter -->
</$set> <!-- searchResults -->
```
",
    "title": "$:/plugins/yaisog/taggingtree-filter/readme",
    "modified": "20230202184645072",
